4.3 SUPRSEND-INSPIRED MULTI-LEVEL PREFERENCES
-----------------------------------------------

Level 1: GLOBAL CHANNEL ON/OFF
  - Push: ON | WhatsApp: ON | Telegram: ON | Email: ON | SMS: OFF

Level 2: CATEGORY PREFERENCES
  - Task Reminders: ON (channels: Push, WhatsApp, Telegram)
  - Daily Content: ON (channels: Push, Telegram)
  - Team Updates: ON (channels: Push, Email)

Level 3: PER-CATEGORY CHANNEL OVERRIDE
  - Task Reminders > WhatsApp: Only for "High Priority" tasks
  - Daily Content > Telegram: Send at 8:00 AM daily

CRITICAL NOTIFICATIONS (cannot be unsubscribed):
  - Account security alerts
  - Payment confirmations
  - Legal/compliance notices
  - Password reset codes


================================================================================
SECTION 5: CONSENT & OPT-IN SCREENS (TRAI, DPDP, GDPR)
================================================================================

5.1 REGULATORY REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------

A) INDIA DPDP ACT 2023

Key Requirements:
- Consent must be: free, specific, informed, unconditional, unambiguous
- Consent must be given through clear affirmative action
- Purpose-specific consent (not bundled)
- Always revocable (withdrawal must be as easy as giving consent)
- Multilingual: Must support all 22 official Indian languages
- WCAG-compliant accessibility
- Consent dashboard: Users must be able to see and withdraw consent at any time
- Layered notices: Must offer simplified + detailed consent notices
- Audio/video notices: For semi-literate users (innovative UX requirement)

UI Implementation Requirements per DPDP BRD (June 2025):
- Granular consent using checkboxes or toggles (per purpose)
- Each processing purpose must have its own consent toggle
- Consent lifecycle management: capture > store > withdraw > re-consent
- Grievance redress mechanism accessible from consent dashboard
- Data retention policy visible to users
- Admin roles for managing organization-level preferences

B) TRAI TCCCPR (TELECOM COMMERCIAL COMMUNICATION)

Key Requirements:
- National Customer Preference Register (NCPR/DND registry) compliance
- DLT (Distributed Ledger Technology) registration mandatory for bulk SMS
- Digital Consent Acquisition (DCA) pilot launched June 2025
- Message suffixes: "P" (Promotional), "S" (Service), "T" (Transactional)
- 7-day consent validity for transactional messages (strict)
- Opt-out in every promotional message
- 90-day cooldown before re-requesting consent from opted-out users
- AI-based monitoring by telecom providers to detect spam patterns
- Penalties: blacklisting, service disconnection up to 1 year, device blocking

C) GDPR (FOR INTERNATIONAL USERS)

Key Requirements:
- Active opt-in (no pre-ticked boxes)
- Granular options per communication type
- Name organization and third parties relying on consent
- Tell users about right to withdraw and how
- Plain language (no legal jargon)
- No dark patterns: fake security badges, guilt-based messaging, visual nudging
- Regulators check HOW consent is obtained, not just that it exists
- Mobile-first consent design is a fundamental requirement

D) CAN-SPAM (FOR US USERS)

Key Requirements:
- Accurate From/Subject header information
- Identify message as advertisement
- Physical postal address of sender
- Opt-out mechanism that processes within 10 business days
- No harvested email addresses
- Responsibility even when using third-party senders


5.2 ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID (DARK PATTERNS)
--------------------------------------------

ILLEGAL/UNETHICAL:
- Pre-ticked consent checkboxes
- "Accept all" button prominent, "Manage" button hidden
- Guilt-tripping copy ("You'll miss important updates!")
- Confusing double negatives ("Uncheck to not receive...")
- Making opt-out harder than opt-in
- Bundled consent (one checkbox for everything)
- Fake urgency ("Enable now or lose access!")
- Misleading toggle labels (ON position means OFF)

LEGAL BUT POOR UX:
- Wall-of-text consent notices
- Legal jargon without plain language alternative
- No withdrawal mechanism visible
- Consent buried in Terms of Service
- No confirmation of consent choices


