SECTION 11: FLUTTER-SPECIFIC IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE
================================================================================

11.1 RECOMMENDED PACKAGE STACK
---------------------------------

QR Code:
- Generation: `qr_flutter` (render QR codes as widgets)
- Scanning: `mobile_scanner` (ML Kit for Android, Apple Vision for iOS)

Phone Input:
- `intl_phone_number_input` (Google libphonenumber, all platforms)
- `country_code_picker` (searchable flags, 70 languages)

OTP Input:
- `pinput` (6 states, autofill, clipboard, theming)
- `sms_otp_auto_verify` (Android SMS Retriever API)

Drag Reorder:
- Flutter `ReorderableListView` (built-in, sufficient for most cases)
- `animated_reorderable_list` (smoother animations)

Progress/Gauges:
- `percent_indicator` (circular + linear, lightweight)
- `syncfusion_flutter_gauges` (advanced radial gauges)
- `fl_chart` (line/bar/pie charts for usage trends)

Connectivity:
- `connectivity_plus` (network type detection)
- `internet_connection_checker_plus` (actual internet verification)

Status Indicators:
- Custom widgets with AnimationController for pulsing effects
- Material 3 Badge widget for status dots on icons

Animations:
- `lottie` (for connection success/failure animations)
- Flutter's built-in AnimatedContainer, AnimatedOpacity, Hero
- `flutter_animate` for declarative animation chains


11.2 STATE MANAGEMENT ARCHITECTURE
------------------------------------

Using Riverpod 3.x (project standard):

Providers:
- channelListProvider: Watches all connected channels from Drift DB
- channelStatusProvider(channelId): Real-time status for specific channel
- notificationPreferencesProvider: Full preference matrix from DB
- quietHoursProvider: Current quiet hours configuration
- fallbackChainProvider: Ordered list of channel priorities
- usageStatsProvider: Monthly usage counts per channel
- consentStateProvider: Current consent status per purpose

State Classes (Freezed):
- ChannelConnection: {id, type, status, lastSync, config, errorMessage}
- NotificationPreference: {categoryId, channelId, enabled, frequency}
- QuietHoursConfig: {workDays, workStart, workEnd, sleepStart, sleepEnd, modes}
- FallbackChain: {orderedChannels, mode, waitTimeBetweenAttempts}
- UsageStats: {channelId, period, sent, limit, cost}
- ConsentRecord: {purpose, granted, grantedAt, version}


11.3 NAVIGATION STRUCTURE
---------------------------

Using go_router (project standard):

/notifications                    -> NotificationHubScreen
/notifications/channels           -> ChannelListScreen
/notifications/channels/:id       -> ChannelDetailScreen
/notifications/channels/add       -> AddChannelScreen
/notifications/channels/add/:type -> ChannelSetupFlow (QR, OTP, etc.)
/notifications/preferences        -> PreferenceMatrixScreen
/notifications/quiet-hours        -> QuietHoursScreen
/notifications/fallback           -> FallbackChainScreen
/notifications/usage              -> UsageQuotaScreen
/notifications/consent            -> ConsentDashboardScreen


11.4 WIDGET TREE ARCHITECTURE
-------------------------------

NotificationHubScreen
+-- SliverAppBar (with search + filter chips)
+-- SliverList
    +-- ActiveChannelsSection
    |   +-- ChannelCard (per connected channel)
    |       +-- ChannelIcon
    |       +-- StatusDot
    |       +-- ProBadge (conditional)
    |       +-- LastSyncTimestamp
    +-- AddChannelCard (+ button with available channels)
    +-- QuickActionsSection
    |   +-- DoNotDisturbChip
    |   +-- QuietHoursChip
    |   +-- TestAllChannelsButton
    +-- UsageSummaryCard
    |   +-- CircularPercentIndicator
    |   +-- ChannelBreakdownBars
    +-- FallbackPreviewCard
        +-- OrderedChannelChips
        +-- "Edit Priority" link


11.5 PERMISSION HANDLING
--------------------------

Notification Permission (Push):
- Request contextually (after user sets up first task, not on app launch)
- Pre-permission screen: "UNJYNX needs notifications to remind you about tasks"
- Show benefit: "Apps that defer permission prompts see 28% higher grant rates"
- If denied: Show banner explaining how to enable in system settings
- Use `permission_handler` package for runtime permission management

Camera Permission (QR Scanning):
- Only requested when user taps "Scan QR Code"
- Pre-permission: "We need camera access to scan the Telegram QR code"
- If denied: Offer "Open in Telegram" as alternative (no camera needed)

SMS Permission (OTP Auto-Read, Android only):
- SMS Retriever API does NOT require SMS permission
- SmartAuth/Pinput handle this automatically
- Never request READ_SMS permission (invasive, unnecessary)


