14.8 ONBOARDING NOTIFICATION PERMISSION STRATEGY
--------------------------------------------------

Based on research showing 28% higher grant rates for deferred permission prompts:

TIMING:
- Do NOT request notification permission on app launch
- Do NOT request during onboarding walkthrough
- DO request AFTER user creates their first task
- Context: "Your task 'Buy groceries' is due tomorrow. Want reminders?"

PRE-PERMISSION SCREEN:
- Custom screen before OS dialog
- Illustration: Phone with friendly notification bubble
- Heading: "Never miss a task again"
- Body: "We'll send you a gentle nudge when tasks are due"
- Benefits: "81% of UNJYNX users who enable reminders complete more tasks"
- [Primary Button]: "Enable Reminders" (triggers OS dialog)
- [Text Link]: "Not now" (skip, ask again after 3rd task creation)

POST-DENIAL RECOVERY:
- If user denies: Show subtle banner on home screen
- Banner: "Reminders are off. Your tasks won't notify you."
- [Link]: "Turn on in Settings"
- Show banner max 3 times, then respect the decision


